 ways of reading the text and the volume as a whole constitutes an important contribution to the growing field of Fanon studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBlack racexPsychology. 0aBlack racexSocial conditions. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh  aCaribbean culture.  aCaribbean history.  aFrantz Fanon.  aOrphée noir.  aPeau noire.  aSartre.  aanti-Black racism.  aanti-Semitism.  acultural significance.  aexistential phenomenology.  ametropolitan France.  apolitical change.  apsychic change.  aracial ideology.  aracism.  auniversalism.  aviolent rupture.1 aBernasconi, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCheyette, Bryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHouse, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebeau, Vicky, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacey, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarriott, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilverman, Max, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilverman, Max, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVergès, Françoise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130693423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130693/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles